WorldStage Newsonline– Union Bank  Plc, one of Nigeria’s oldest bank  on Monday informed the Nigerian Stock Exchange and the investing public that Mrs. Furera Isma Jumare, an Independent Non-Executive Director on its  Board had resigned following her appointment as the Director General of the Jigawa State Investment Promotion Agency. Union Bank in a notice signed by Somuyiwa Sonubi, Company Secretary said she resigned in line with Central Bank of Nigeria guidelines with effect from 15th October 2020. “The Bank has commenced the process of filling her seat and further communication will be made as soon as the Board confirms a replacement,” the notice filed at the NSE said.